The paper deals with formal abstractions of a Markov process and its approximation by a finite-state Markov chain. This involves computation of average transition probabilities between partition sets. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of control theory, artificial intelligence, machine learning, and information theory, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IT, and cs.NE. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
